    'portfolio.pulse.details': 'This section adds context to the case studies: what constraints appeared, what prototypes tested them, and how decisions moved into later products.\n\n## R&D lines\n\n- MEGAVISOR -> PhotoPizza: from a cloud 360-media platform and field production work to an open-source motorized turntable for repeatable capture, video, and photogrammetry.\n- PhotoPizza -> ComplexScan -> AUTOBOX v1: motion control, lighting, and workflow automation started as an open-source hardware base, then became commercial equipment and museum-grade 3D scanning technology.\n- BoothBot: applied automation of a client warehouse process, where equipment, light, camera motion, and photo processing had to work without a studio team.\n- Agent Portal and MCP tools: the same R&D method moved into software - context engineering, RAG-style retrieval, context compression, project graphs, model/resource routing, multi-agent orchestration, tool use, evals/guardrails, observability, audit gates, and loop engineering.\n- Confidential platforms: private projects are described by task type, architecture, and result, without client names or internal identifiers.\n\n## How to read the notes\n\nA project card shows the finished result. A journal note shows the research path: the original constraint, the practical prototype, the real-process validation, and the move to the next system.',
