    'portfolio.skills.details': '## Skill concentration\n\n- R&D / product engineering: domain research, constraint discovery, architecture, prototyping, field validation, release discipline, and turning unclear tasks into operational systems.\n- AI tooling and agents: Agent Portal, MCP/tool use, WebMCP, context engineering, RAG-style retrieval, context compression, project graphs, multi-agent orchestration, model/resource routing, tool contracts, structured execution state, browser evidence, eval-style checks, guardrails, observability, and audit gates.\n- Full-stack / platform: JavaScript, Node.js, Web/PWA, Web Components, API services, PostgreSQL, WebSocket runtime sync, PM2/nginx operations, deployment scripts, SSH/WebSocket tunnels, and practical adaptation to unfamiliar frontend/backend/runtime/ops stacks including Python when needed.\n- Product UI: admin panels, dashboards, editors, graph interfaces, design systems, provider metadata, component contracts, responsive tool surfaces, and workflows that turn prototypes into daily-use products.\n- Backend/ops and messaging: lifecycle messaging, opt-in SMS scenarios, campaign orchestration, audience segmentation, analytics, internal roles, GSM modem pools, serial/AT-command control, SMS inbox/USSD operations, and repeatable business workflows.\n- Media and hardware capability: 360 media, photogrammetry, controlled light, controlled motion, STM32/ESP32 experiments, field capture workflows, physical prototypes, early production, and process automation for real environments.',
    'portfolio.skill.rnd.details': '## R&D / product engineering\n\n- Research unclear domains, find real constraints, separate assumptions from field evidence, and define the smallest useful prototype.\n- Design product and technical architecture around the actual workflow, not around a preferred stack.\n- Move from prototype to operational process: validation, documentation, release gates, audit loops, cleanup, and practical handoff.\n- Work across software, AI tooling, media workflows, backend/ops, and physical systems when the task needs it.',
    'portfolio.skill.agenticAi.details': '## AI tooling / agent systems\n\n- Build agent-operable environments: Agent Portal, MCP servers, tool contracts, browser evidence, terminal automation, and resource-aware orchestration.\n- Practice context engineering: project memory, RAG-style retrieval, context compression, graph-based project structure, and compact handoff data for stronger models.\n- Optimize agent work by routing simpler tasks to faster/cheaper models and reserving stronger models for decisions that need broader context.\n- Use structured execution state, eval-style checks, guardrails, observability, audit gates, and human-in-the-loop control to keep agent work verifiable.',
    'portfolio.skill.productUi.details': '## Product interfaces\n\n- Build product portals, admin panels, dashboards, editors, graph tools, media tools, and operational interfaces for repeated use.\n- Use Web/PWA, Web Components, provider metadata, reusable UI contracts, responsive layouts, and browser-visible evidence as part of the engineering process.\n- Design interfaces for scanning, comparison, repeated action, review loops, and practical team workflows rather than decorative presentation.',
